        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/meaghan1">@meaghan1</a></p>
<p>OK, I tried it out locally and got the same as you. I did a bit of digging and this seems to work:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">useEffect(() =&gt; {
    actions.source.fetch("/blog");
  }, []);
</code></pre>
<p>Add this in the component for the individual blog and then you should see the posts in the Frontity state.</p>
<p>Let me know if this does the trick for you.</p>
