      <item>
        <title>Adding related posts to post page template</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/meaghan1">@meaghan1</a></p>
<p>The <code>isPostArchive</code> will be there if the page is a post archive, i.e. a blog listing page. I used <code>/blog/</code> in my example, but you need to put the slug of whatever page is your blog listing page - i.e. whatever page you’ve defined as the <code>Posts page</code> in the WordPress admin <code>Settings -&gt; Reading</code> page:</p>
<p></p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5abe9c51ca5899987eae5b5436948ad4dab8eb06.png" data-download-href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/5abe9c51ca5899987eae5b5436948ad4dab8eb06" title="image"><img src="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/5abe9c51ca5899987eae5b5436948ad4dab8eb06_2_690x253.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="cWLlVGCnlHpiry6TlP4Bp5dy8gC" width="690" height="253" srcset="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/5abe9c51ca5899987eae5b5436948ad4dab8eb06_2_690x253.png, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/5abe9c51ca5899987eae5b5436948ad4dab8eb06_2_1035x379.png 1.5x, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5abe9c51ca5899987eae5b5436948ad4dab8eb06.png 2x" data-small-upload="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/5abe9c51ca5899987eae5b5436948ad4dab8eb06_2_10x10.png"></a></div><p></p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/adding-related-posts-to-post-page-template/2798/8">Read full topic</a></p>
