      <item>
        <title>Adding related posts to post page template</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>I don’t see the <code>isPostArchive</code> property there. Have you got your homepage set to a page? Like this in <code>frontity.settings.js</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">{
      "name": "@frontity/wp-source",
      "state": {
        "source": {
          "api": "https://mysite.com/wp-json",
          "homepage": "home",
          "postsPage": "blog"
        }
      }
    },
</code></pre>
<p>If so you will need to put in the path to the posts page, so something like this:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">const data = state.source.get('/blog/');
</code></pre>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/adding-related-posts-to-post-page-template/2798/6">Read full topic</a></p>
