<pre><code class="lang-javascript">const data = state.source.get(state.router.link);
console.log(data);
</code></pre>
<p>On a typical page, say the home page, the above code returns an array of posts. But when I use the same code above on the Post.js page, it only returns an object with current post data such as id, slug, post type. But I would like to be able to return the original post array that I can get on the home page. This is so that I can display a section of related posts in the Post.js component.</p>
